		"name": "unisouk-assignment",
		"description": "# 🚀 UniSouk Assignment Integration - Postman Guide\n\n### 📌 Overview\n\nThis collection tests the integration between **NestJS** and **OpenCart 4.x**. It covers Product management, Order processing, and automated Inventory synchronization.\n\n### ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Authentication & OpenCart 4.x\n\n- **Skip Authentication Folder:** You can proceed directly to the main modules (**Products, Orders, Inventory**).\n    \n- **Bridge Support:** I have implemented a **Bridge Secret** mechanism. This allows the NestJS app to communicate directly with OpenCart without relying on the legacy OpenCart API login, which is often unstable or unsupported in version 4.x.\n    \n- **Why the Auth Folder exists:** I have kept the \"Authentication\" folder strictly for **demonstration/comparison purposes**. It proves that the standard OpenCart 4.x API login route is non-functional or inconsistent in this version. **Do not use this folder for functional testing.**\n    \n\n---\n\n### 🏃‍♂️ How to Test (One-Click Runner)\n\nFor the most efficient review, please use the **\"Test this E2E flow with runner\"** folder. This folder contains automated logic that performs a full system lifecycle test in one go.\n\n**The Runner performs the following steps automatically:**\n\n1. **Create Product:** Registers a fresh product in the system.\n    \n2. **Check Stock:** Records the initial inventory level.\n    \n3. **Create Order:** Places a new order against the product created in Step 1.\n    \n4. **Sync Trigger:** Updates the order status to \"Processing\" to trigger the background sync worker.\n    \n5. **Final Verification:** Mathematically verifies that the inventory was correctly decremented in the database.\n    \n\n**To run it:**\n\n1. Click on the **\"Test this E2E flow with runner\"** folder.\n    \n2. Click the **\"Run\"** button in the top right.\n    \n3. Click **\"Run unisouk-assignment\"**.\n    \n4. Watch the test results (all should be green).\n    \n\n---\n\n### 🛠 Configuration (Variables)\n\nEnsure your **Collection Variables** are set correctly:\n\n- base_url: http://localhost:3000 (Your NestJS Server)\n    \n- opencart_base_url: http://localhost:8080 (Your OpenCart Installation)\n    \n- opencart_bridge_secret: Your defined secret for the bridge connection.\n    \n\n### 📁 Folder Structure\n\n- **Authentication:** (Optional/Reference) Demonstrates OC 4.x legacy API limitations.\n    \n- **Products:** CRUD operations for product management.\n    \n- **Orders:** Order retrieval and status update logic.\n    \n- **Inventory:** Dedicated endpoints for stock levels and low-stock alerts.\n    \n- **Test this E2E flow with runner:** Automated end-to-end testing logic.",
